This involves assessing acoustic capabilities and ensuring the power supply can handle the event’s AV demands proficiently.

Another significant oversight is the lack of communication between your crew and the venue’s management, leading to mismatches in expectations and execution. Establishing clear channels of communication with each stakeholder can mitigate errors.

It’s all about aligning your AV company with the venue’s logistical constraints while considering the intricacies of the event production timeline. **Malaga Event Gear (MEG)**’s expert AV team advises preemptively engaging with venue staff to adapt setups to fit the venue’s scope and capabilities. This foresight can greatly reduce operational hiccups on the event day.

